                <li>All federal, state and local laws and regulations apply.</li></ul>
                <p><strong>Eligibility: </strong></p>
                <ul><li>The Video Scholarship Contest is open to United States and international students and anyone with outstanding student loans, 18 years or older. The contest is offered to all fields of study.</li>
                <li>Each participant must register at http://www.gotchosen.com, and create his/ her entry for the contest. A participant is defined as an individual, not a group.</li>
                <li>The winners will be notified by the e-mail address provided.</li>
                <li>There is no cost to enter, and eligibility is not based on financial need or academic performance.</li>
                <li>Only one (1) video submission per participant is permitted.</li>
                <li>Each participant must upload their video to YouTube, and then paste the link in the “Create New Entry” form.</li>
                <li>We recommend videos under 3 minutes. Supported YouTube file formats are: .MOV, .MPEG4, .AVI, .WMV, .MPEGPS, .FLV, 3GPP, and WebM.</li>
                <li>Only the one (1) participant submitting the video is eligible for the scholarship. The video may contain an unlimited number of people of any age, but only the participant submitting the video will be eligible to win.</li>
                <li>Video must be original, and the participant must have the rights to any and all  media used. Videos must not infringe on any third-party rights or copyrights. If GotChosen receives a notice of copyright infringements from the owner of the material, the video in violation will be removed.</li>
                <li>Be advised - utilizing media that infringes on any copyright in this Video Scholarship Contest will not constitute “Fair Use” in accordance to the United States Code Title 17, Chapter 1, Section 107.</li>
                <li>Videos submitted for prior GotChosen contests are eligible for entry into the contest.</li>
                <li>Employees of GotChosen, Inc., their respective parents, immediate family members, and persons living in the households of each of these individuals, whether related or not, are ineligible for this drawing.</li>
                <li>The contest is subject to all applicable federal, state, and local laws and regulations, and the contest is void where prohibited or restricted by law.</li>
                <li>Fraud Prevention: Each video can be voted on once a day per IP address.</li>
                <li>Videos that are deemed to be immoral, obscene, profane; sexually explicit or suggestive; unnecessarily violent or derogatory of an ethnic, racial, gender, religious, professional or age group; pornographic; contain nudity; promote alcohol, illegal drugs, tobacco, firearms/weapons; promote particular political agenda or message; endorse forms of hate or a hate group; or not in keeping with GotChosen's image; or are in violation of these Official Rules, may be disqualified and the video removed.</li>
                <li>GotChosen reserves the right to remove any video and the entry for the contest that contains content that is deemed offensive in accordance to the specifications outlined in these rules and regulations and at its sole discretion.</li>
                <li>Entries that appear to duplicate any other submitted entries will be void and only the first entry submitted (based on time/date) will be included in the Contest.</li></ul>
                <p><strong>Contest Details:</strong></p>
                <p>The Season 3 Lights, Camera, Action Video Scholarship Contest will begin on January 20, 2014. Participants will be able to create their entries for the public to view and vote for their favorite video. The public voting period will end on April 21, 2014 at 11:59:59 p.m. EDT. </p>
                <p>All of the videos will be displayed in a random order throughout the whole contest.</p>
                <p>The number of votes received for each video will be tracked by GotChosen’s platform, and the Top 3 videos with the most votes will win. The video with the most votes will win a US $2,500 scholarship and the next 2 runner ups will each win a US $250 scholarship.</p>
                <p>Each participant will see their current number of votes, privately displayed, on their profile page. </p>
                <p><strong>To Enter:</strong></p>
                <p>In order to create your entry for the video contest, first, you must upload your video to YouTube, and then go to the GotChosen.com to create your entry (your YouTube video link will be required to complete your entry). </p>
                <p><strong>Existing GotChosen users</strong> simply need to Login, and create your entry for the Video Scholarship contest from one of the following 5 categories: </p>
                <ol><li>Doing Good: reveal who has inspired you to change the world</li>
                <li>Let Me Dance: show us your best dance moves </li>
                <li>The Downfall of Internet Privacy: tell us how you see the general invasion of privacy on the internet</li>
                <li>Sports: capture the greatest sports moment of you or your friends </li>
                <li>Fake Commercial: make up a commercial for a fake movie or TV show</li></ol>
                <p><strong>New visitors to GotChosen must</strong>: (1) complete an on-line registration and (2) create your entry for the Video Scholarship contest based on the available 5 categories listed above.</p>
                By completing and submitting their entry, participants acknowledge and agree to the Rules and Regulations herein and to GotChosen’s Privacy Policy.
